&lt;p&gt;Are you newly qualified nurse looking to start your career in supportive, innovative and fast pacing environment? Or you may be experienced nurse looking to develop your skills and knowledge in a variety of specialties such as stoma nursing, tissue viability or pain management?&lt;br /&gt;If you answered yes then please join us at the Damson ward. Damson ward is an acute surgical ward with expertise in bowel and colorectal surgery.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We offer you: &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;-Newly qualified nurses are automatically enrolled onto 18 months individually tailored preceptorship including 8 core study days and access to bespoke training package.&lt;br /&gt;-Opportunity to transfer (after 9 months) to different specialty or division.&lt;br /&gt;-On-going learning and development including access to mentorship and leadership courses.&lt;br /&gt;-Clearly structured career pathway in preparation towards band 6.&lt;br /&gt;-On-going support from enthusiastic and innovative team and dedicated Clinical Practice Educator &lt;br /&gt;-Assistance with accommodation &lt;br /&gt;-Keep Fit scheme&lt;br /&gt;-Childcare vouchers and nursery&lt;br /&gt;-Working at The World renowned Trust graded Good by CQC&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sister Marva Sammy &lt;br /&gt;Email: marva.sammy@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;Telephone: 02082165267&lt;/p&gt;
